Blocks.childText: 218-19] SANCTIFICATION. 197 218 S. M. W. Thompson. THE SAME. W HY should I fear thy foes, Or tremble at the sound ? The Lord my God I've set apart- He guards my soul around. 2 Though I am poor and weak, And lame, and blind withal, Through God my soul shall never faint, Nor shall I ever fall. 3 This all my answer is, When reasons are required, Why such a wretch as I should hope : My God my hope inspired. 4 Let proud imperial kings Their bloody swords display ; Or erring sects, with flattering baits, More subtle far than they :- 5 Let earth and Satan join, And death and sin annoy : In God alone I put my trust- He gives me inward joy. 6 Ye Saints lift up your heads, Let joy fill every heart; For as your never-failing all, You have set God apart. ADOPTION. 219 S. M. Watts. HUMILITY OF SOUL UNDER THE HOPE OF ADOP. TION. John III, 1. Gal. IV, 6. B EHOLD, what wonderous grace The Father has bestowed On sinners of a mortal race, To call them sons of God.
